FBIS4-35933 "drnes108_j_94029" FBIS-NES-94-108 Daily Report 5 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Saudi Statements Said To `Delay' Cease-Fire Saudi Statements Said To `Delay' Cease-Fire JN0506124794 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1200 GMT 5 Jun 94 JN0506124794 Paris Radio Monte Carlo Arabic BFN [Text] Sanaa has announced that it will delay its decision to accept a cease-fire, as demanded by the United Nations, as a result of Saudi statements that the Arabian Gulf states may move if battles in Yemen continue. This was announced by a northern official, who said verbatim that Sanaa was about to officially inform the UN secretary general of its agreement on a cease-fire, but that Saudi Foreign Minister Sa'ud al-Faysal's statements delayed that announcement.
